Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for drizzling}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, quarter, core and grate the @apple{1/2}(quartered, cored and grated) (no need to peel). In a large #bowl{}, combine the apple, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}.

Once cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the burger buns into your oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to a medium bowl. Drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%g}. Toss to evenly coat the rocket.

When everything's ready, spread the @apple and sage jelly{25%g} over the bun bases. Top with the cheesy burgers, crispy @British streaky bacon{4%rashers} and the bun lids.

Serve your pork and apple burger with the rosemary wedges and salad alongside.

Enjoy!